<LP>
   TORONTO -- Scott's Hospitality Inc. said it bought
Britain's largest take-out and delivery pizza chain, with
more than 40% of the British market, from Grand Metropolitan
PLC. Terms weren't disclosed.
   Scott's said the Perfect Pizza chain comprises four
company stores and 150 franchised units, with total sales of
25 million to 30 million British pounds ($47.5 million to $57
million) annually.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Scott's is a food-service, hotel, photography,
transportation and warehousing concern. Grand Metropolitan is
a food, liquor and retailing company.
</TEXT>
